description: This project emphasized my thesis implementation which was part of my university thesis.Thesis Title: An Adaptation Middleware Supporting Continuous Adaptation of End User Driven Application Composition Framework

name: java-microservice-reference
description: This repository can be used as a reference to write well-designed, layered Spring Boot applications. This repository has a standard 3-tier application architecture which you can use to build any standard springboot-based microservice application. This also covers TDD approach using Mockito. Lombok integration makes this application easy in case of code refactoring. The repository is built based on an excellent book - Learn Microservices with Spring Boot.

name: aws-serverless-announcement-microservice
description: A small serverless application (MicroService) exposes JSON formatted REST APIs which allow for storing and retrieving announcements.

name: ang-games
description: This application is an attempt to find a general algorithm for solving a kind of mathematical chess problem known as “independence problem”, such as the Eight Queen puzzle. This algorithm tries to discover how many possible solutions exist.

name: Dining-Concierge
description: Customer Service is an important service for a lot of businesses around the world. In this application, we have implemented a serverless, microservice driven web application to suggest dining options. We have developed a dining concierge chatbot, which learns the user preference of cuisines, date and time and gives restaurant suggestions.
